		<hr size="1">/e hands the wood elf a batwing crunchie</P><P>Easy there..... I'm a druid as well, and yes I'm not to thrilled about the books either... Just not for the same reasons.</P><P>I can still make some plat porting people to stoneburnt (to get players to LoY zones) and good old CS for some wyvern hunting, but most of the time if Im not doing anything I'll port for free.</P><P>/e ducks </P><P>Okay... The real reason why I'm not happy with the books is that it has taken a lot of the adventure out of the game.  Used to be quite a run to get to The Overthere.  But now, click a book.  In Butcherblock and want to go to Freeport? Take a boat? Not now.. How about FV zone to go into the LoIO? Granted not as many people hunt there in their mid 20s or so any more, but some people are realizing that sometimes, the old ways can be the best ways (see about the battle wizzard later in my post *shudder*)</P><P>Used to take time to get to places.  It has, in my opinion, made the game more for the 'just give it to me now, I don't realy want to work for it' kind of player.  You know the kind.. The people who don't play their class well because they got PLed from day one.  Like a battle wizzard (yeah... you heard me) who would rather melee than cast because that way he won't get hit by the mob.</P><P>*sigh*</P><P>/e goes back to making batwing crunchies....</P><P><BR><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="http://www.geocities.com/cptqrk/banner.jpg.txt"></P><P>wanna see my junk?<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=724376" TARGET="_BLANK">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=724376</A></P><P>Message edited by: Summoner of Pets (9/23/2003 8:44:27 AM)<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
