		<hr size="1">Hmmm...I think I actually make MORE money now porting than I ever did. Don't get me wrong, you'll never make a living off it, but now people only want to port to higher lvl places that don't have a PoK book. These places tend to garner larger donations than the others...so for those druids who wanted to lvl up and get they're first few ports, don't go around /ooc'ing. That's not intelligent. Lvl up more, get all of your ports, then when someone /oocs "WTB Port to Cobalt Scar, paying 100p" you can /tell "Kind sir, I would gladly take you there." bring him, and be off your way. </P><P>Not many people /ooc anymore. That business is largely over, which is fantastic. All that spam was rediculous. People wouldn't put it on /auc, so you couldn't really block it out if you wanted to keep /ooc, which i always like to have up. Now, mostly people just /ooc or /auc wanting to buy ports, and that way get people who aren't busy. And, that way druids and wizzies don't have to sit around all day looking for ports. They can port someone fast, get 20-50 pp on avg, then head off to group. </P><P>_________________________________________</P><P>As for the adventure part, I absolutely agree with you. However, I like the idea of PoK and the books. What they should have done is make it like LDoN, where you need to get keyed to be able to use the books. Would have been responsible, and not an 'easy way out,' yet not making people do hours and hours of travelling. The quest should have been like an hour long quest, not an easy one, that way some people would rather just not do the quest if it wasn't important to them, or do the quest if it was. Mostly talking to merchants and stuff, I don't think it should require killing. People over lvl 15 should be able to do it. That's my 2cp anyway. </P><P>The one thing that I don't like about PoK is the fact that it trivialized the nexus. Now the nexus isn't really a nexus of travelling, its just some empty zone like all the rest of them now. You used to be able to go there and get anything, get ports from the scions, ports from players, kei and other buffs, go to the best zones in the game for the appropriate lvl...now its mostly empty. Maybe 15 people will be there when its fairly busy. Only people that are headng to the bazaar, NL,  or shadowheaven tend to be there. It's kind of sad, maybe in a similar way it is sad that EC is/was empty (it isn't anymore, w/LDoN, but you all know what I mean). I began playing just a little while after luclin, so I've only known the bazaar. </P><P>eh, I guess that's why they put the 'warning, this game will change over time' thingy on when logging in. <br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
