		<hr size="1">PS: Summoner of Pets -- Couldn't you get the same excitement from going to any new zone? The first time I see any new monster I think it's pretty neat. People can still see giants in other zones, even named ones.</P><P>Yes, I do get that kind of excitement, but you do have to admit that Sony has 'dumbed down' the newbie game. Look to the last patch for example:</P><P><BR>All nubs start with<BR>food & water, same old same old <img src='http://www.everlore.com/gimages/smile.gif' width=15 height=15 align=middle></P><P>First two spells, SCRIBED AND MEMED</P><P>Sense Heading of 200, right off the bat, /sigh so much for having to learn your Norathian geography</P><P>Bandages, fine... never used them anyways</P><P>Backpack, to "help demonstrate the use of containers" </P><P>If Sony was so worried about 'demonstrating' to new players then why don't they PUT THE TUTORIAL BACK IN!?</P><P>/sigh</P><P>I think my real gripe is that the experiance that I had as a newbie is lost on the people who are picking up EQ for the first time, I guess I just want to share that same kind of awe that I felt when I first realized just how HUGE the world that was created really is.  Running with SoW across South Karana, taking the boat *gasp i know*. I'm just of the school of thought that if you just give everything to someone they will never really learn it.</P><P>I'm not a 'bible thumper' but the old saying<BR>"give a man a fish, and he will eat for one night,<BR>teach a man to fish and he will feed himelf forever"<BR>rings true, especially in games like this.  If everything is just handed to you, then what are you doing? Going through the motions, not learning how to use your class to it's fullest poetential, be it a druid or not.</P><P>I'm going to stop posting on this thread now, as I beleive that I have expressed my feelings and thoughts to the best of my abilities.  My only hope is that some of the posters who say "woot books ro>&lt;>&lt;ors" (I know.. no one really said this) can also see from the other side, and maybe remember back to when they first saw the land of Norrath, and /boggled at the immense adventure that lay before them instead of pulling up a map and head off to a book.</P><P>May you get out of the game what you wish.</P><P>****Edit** ACK!!! Forgot my summoner of pets login and used an old one LOL Mil is my mage on CT hehe I should dust off the cobwebs on her some day.</P><P></P><P>Message edited by: Milreni the Gnome (11/8/2003 11:46:57 PM)<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
